719862f-a.title: Manhattan: Fort Washington Park - [Lighthouse.]
719862f-a.text:
Fort Washington Park: A View showing Manhattan's only
lighthouse nestling beneath the Weorge Washington Bridge. This
sets on a promontory formerly known as Jeffery's Hook. A moon
shaned battery, built here in 1775, overlooked the spot where
ships were sunk to cbstruct the British Tleet during the American
Revolution.
October 21, 1938
George D. Chinn
NO RETi.ODUOTTIONST
